Package gaffer.function.simple.filter

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AgeOff
    An AgeOff is a SimpleFilterFunction that ages off old data based on a provided age of time in milliseconds.
    And
    An And is a MultiFilterFunction that should be created with a list of ConsumerFunctionContext contain FilterFunctions.
    AreEqual
    An AreEqual is a FilterFunction that returns true if the two input objects are equal.
    Exists
    An Exists is a SimpleFilterFunction that simply checks the input object is not null.
    HyperLogLogPlusIsLessThan
    An Exists is a SimpleFilterFunction that simply checks that the input HyperLogLogPlus cardinality is less than a control value.
    IsEqual
    An IsEqual is a SimpleFilterFunction that checks that the input object is equal to a control value.
    IsFalse
    An IsFalse is a SimpleFilterFunction that checks that the input boolean is false.
    IsIn
    An IsIn is a SimpleFilterFunction that checks that the input object is in a set of allowed values.
    IsLessThan
    An IsLessThan is a SimpleFilterFunction that checks that the input Comparable is less than a control value.
    IsMoreThan
    An IsMoreThan is a SimpleFilterFunction that checks that the input Comparable is more than a control value.
    IsShorterThan
    An IsShorterThan is a SimpleFilterFunction that checks that the input object has a length less than a maximum length.
    IsTrue
    An IsTrue is a SimpleFilterFunction that checks that the input boolean is true.
    IsXLessThanY
    An IsXLessThanY is a FilterFunction that checks that the first input Comparable is less than the second input Comparable.
    IsXMoreThanY
    An IsXMoreThanY is a FilterFunction that checks that the first input Comparable is more than the second input Comparable.
    MapContains
    An MapContains is a SimpleFilterFunction that checks whether a Map contains a provided key.
    MultiRegex  
    Not
    An Not is a FilterFunction that wraps a FilterFunction, and inverts the result from the wrapped function.
    Or
    An Or is a MultiFilterFunction that should be created with a list of ConsumerFunctionContext contain FilterFunctions.
    Regex
